.com/us/album/everyday-life/1484143590|title=Everyday Life by Coldplay|website=Apple Music|accessdate=11 November 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Coldplay}}\n\n[[Category:2019 albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Rik Simpson]]\n[[Category:Coldplay albums]]\n[[Category:Atlantic Records albums]]\n[[Category:Parlophone albums]]\n", "name_user": "2a02:c7f:601d:a100:7c11:3325:726b:c0b5", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Everyday_Life_(Coldplay_album)"}
{"title_page": "2009 RFL Championship", "text_new": "{{Infobox rugby football league season\n|title= Co-operative Championship 2009\n|league=[[Co-operative Championship]]\n|logo=\n|pixels=190px\n|caption=The Co-operative Championship competition logo\n|duration=\n|no_of_teams=11\n|attendance= 217,362 (average 1,874)\n|TV=\n|season=2009 Season\n|season_champs= {{leagueicon|Barrow|16}}  [[Barrow Raiders]]\n|season_champ_name= Season Champions\n|league_leaders= {{leagueicon|Barrow|16}}  [[Barrow Raiders]]\n|league_leaders_name= League Leaders\n|second_place= {{leagueicon|Halifax|16}}  [[Halifax R.L.F.C.|Halifax]]\n|MVP=\n|MVP_link=Man of Steel Award\n|top_scorer=\n|top_scorer_link=\n|top try scorer=\n|top try scorer_link=\n|promote  =\n|promoted_from  =\n|relegate= [[Leigh Centurions]](Subsequently Reprieved)<br />[[Doncaster R.L.F.C.|Doncaster]]<br />[[Gateshead Thunder (2000)|Gateshead Thunder]](Subsequently Disqualified)\n|relegate_to= [[RFL League 1|Championship 1]]\n|playoffs=\n|playoffs_link=\n|conf1=\n|conf1_link=\n|conf1_champ=\n|conf1-runner-up=\n|conf2=\n|conf2_link=\n|conf2_champ=\n|conf2-runner-up=\n|playoffs_MVP=\n|playoffs_MVP_link=\n|finals=\n|finals_link=\n|finals_champ=\n|finals-runner-up=\n|finals_MVP=\n|finals_MVP_link=\n|prevseason_link=Rugby League National Leagues in 2008\n|prevseason_year=2008\n|nextseason_link=2010 RFL Championship\n|nextseason_year=2010\n}}\nThe '''2009 Co-operative Championship''' is a semi-professional [[rugby league|rugby league football]] competition played in the [[United Kingdom]] and [[France]] one tier below the first tier [[Super League]]. The two worst performing teams during the season, with the exception of [[Toulouse Olympique]], will be relegated to [[RFL League 1|Championship 1]].\n\nThere is no automatic promotion from this league to Super League, which uses a licensing system renewed every three years. Qualifying for the Grand Final is a prerequisite for Championship clubs to be able to apply for license in the next round of applications for the [[2012\u201314 Super League licences|2012\u201314 period]].\n\nThe competition was very close with most teams having a chance of making the top 6 going into the final round. In the end [[Barrow Raiders]] topped the standings followed by [[Halifax R.L.F.C.|Halifax]]. The [[Leigh Centurions]] were relegated on the final day of competition despite finishing only third to last and [[Doncaster R.L.F.C.|Doncaster]] were also relegated but their fate had been sealed for some time. In the weeks following the competitions completion, Gateshead Thunder were eliminated following salary cap breaches and subsequently relegated to the Championship 1 for 2010, Leigh Centurions were therefore reprieved from relegation and remained in the Championship for 2010.\n\nIn the playoffs, [[Widnes Vikings]] and [[Featherstone Rovers]] advance from the first week to play each other. Featherstone won this game which gave them the chance to take on Halifax, who lost their game to Barrow, for a spot in the grand final. Halifax won and went on to play Barrow in the final but lost 26-18.\n\n==Table==\n{{RFL National Championship 2009 Ladder}}\n\n==Play-offs==\n\nThe Co-operative Championship uses a [[Top six play-offs|top 6 play-off system]].\n\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"3\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; font-size:80%; text-align:center; width:100%;\"\n|- style=\"background:#c1d8ff;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:19%;\"|Home\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:6%;\"|Score\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:19%;\"|Away\n!colspan=6|Match Information\n|- style=\"background:#ccc;\"\n!width=17%|Date and Time\n!width=19%|Venue\n!width=13%|Referee\n!width=7%|Attendance\n\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n|align=left | {{leagueicon|Widnes|23px}} [[Widnes Vikings]]\n|26 \u2013 21\n|align=left | {{leagueicon|Whitehaven|23px}} [[Whitehaven R.L.F.C.|Whitehaven]]\n|10 September, 19:30 GMT\n|[[Halton Stadium|Stobart Stadium]]\n|\n|  2,375\n|- style=\"back